Now,
 $$
\mathbf{b}=\dfrac12\mathbf a+\dfrac{3\sqrt2}2\mathbf c\tag{1}
$$ Morover, since $\mathbf b$ is their angle bisector, $$
|\mathbf c|=\sigma|\mathbf a| \implies \sigma=\dfrac{|\mathbf c|}{|\mathbf a|}=\dfrac2{\sqrt7}\tag{2}
$$ Therefore, $$
\mathbf c=2\left(\mathbf b\mp\dfrac{3\sqrt2}7\mathbf a\right)\tag{3}
$$ or, if you like, $$
\mathbf c=\dfrac{3\sqrt2}3\mathbf a\mp\dfrac{25}7\mathbf b\tag{3'}
$$ [answer]$\color{blue}{2\left(\mathbf b\pm\dfrac{3\sqrt2}7\mathbf a\right)}$

